"script": "Volunteers were told to press a button that delivered electric shocks to a stranger in the next room. With every wrong answer, the voltage climbed higher. Soon the stranger was screaming, pounding the wall, begging them to stop. But a calm man in a lab coat simply said, please continue. And shockingly, most people obeyed, turning the dial all the way to a level marked lethal. The stranger was an actor. The shocks were fake. But the obedience was terrifyingly real. The experiment proved something chilling: ordinary people will hurt others badly, just because someone in authority told them to.",
